# Lab09: heap-ovfl

In this week, you will learn the way of exploiting heap-related
vulnerabilities; in short, these are the memory bugs related to malloc() (not
local variables on the stack). It is a bit comlicated, however, once you get the
core idea, you will truly be able to understand how the applications behave.

* Problems

  + [level 00] tut09-heap           [20 points]
  + [level 01] dlmalloc             [20 points]
  + [level 02] ptmalloc             [20 points]
  + [level 03] uaf-basic            [20 points]
  + [level 04] heap-spray           [20 points]
  + [level 05] linked-list          [20 points]
  + [level 06] registration         [20 points]
  + [level 07] storage              [20 points]
  + [level 08] force                [20 points]
  + [level 09] spirit               [20 points]
  + [level 10] linked-list2         [20 points]
  + [level 11] tut09-advheap        [20 points]

